We used the CSLB [cslb] dataset, a large crowdsourced set of basic CSK assertions, like alligator: is scary / is long / is green. We focused on the top 4,245 properties for 638 subjects stated at least five times. For each corpus, we computed the relative frequencies with which these statements appear (w/ lemmatization).